There is a javascript error when attempting to create a project. The culprit is:
{code}
/plugins/project-templates-plugin/1.7.1/project-templates-plugin-1.7.1.jar!/js/DialogController.js

JPT.DialogController.hideDialogFromNewUser = function hideDialogFromNewUser() {
    return $.ajax({ //This! Have to use AJS.$ instead of just $
        url: JPT.DialogController.welcomeRestUrl,
        type: "DELETE",
        success: function () {
            AJS.log("don't show project template dialog anymore");
        }
    });
};
{code}

Previously this has gone unnoticed because another plugin somewhere in JIRA is overriding the global $ variable and hence exposing it to the rest of the plugins. Things may have changed during 6.0. 
Not exposing $ is actually the intended behaviour, plugins should have used AJS.$ anyway.

To reproduce:
1. Start a JIRA OD-11 instance
2. Disable the feedback plugin (this is the plugin exposing $)
3, Attempt to create a new project via the browse project page


Workaround:
The customer can Enable 'JIRA Feedback Plugin' which exposes '$', so project-templates-plugin can use it

Steps to reproduce:
# Administer a project.
# Click "Team shortcuts".

You will be presented with an error
{quote}
h3. Unauthorized (401)
{panel}
Encountered a "401 - Unauthorized" error while loading this page.
{panel}
